Пользователь получает кэшбэк 2% на месячный оборот до 500 AZN и 1% кэшбэка на оборот превышающий 500 AZN - Пользователь оплачивает <providerName> на сумму до и свыше 500 AZN единовременно и получает 0% кэшбэка - Примеры.Лимит кэшбэка.   - java.lang.Double -> DoubleComparator[precision=1.0E-15]
  - java.lang.Float -> FloatComparator[precision=1.0E-6]
  - java.nio.file.Path -> lexicographic comparator (Path natural order)
- actual and expected objects and their fields were compared field by field recursively even if they were not of the same type, this allows for example to compare a Person to a PersonDto (call strictTypeChecking(true) to change that behavior).

actual and expected values are collections of different size, actual size=0 when expected size=4

The recursive comparison was performed with this configuration:
- all expected null fields were ignored in the comparison
- the following fields were ignored in the comparison: missionType, hasProgress, bonusAmount, missionOrder, imageUrl, shortTitle, shortDescription, title, description, textPath
- no overridden equals methods were used in the comparison (except for java types)
- these types were compared with the following comparators:
  - java.lang.Double -> DoubleComparator[precision=1.0E-15]
  - java.lang.Float -> FloatComparator[precision=1.0E-6]
  - java.nio.file.Path -> lexicographic comparator (Path natural order)
- actual and expected objects and their fields were compared field by field recursively even if they were not of the same type, this allows for example to compare a Person to a PersonDto (call strictTypeChecking(true) to change that behavior).
